name: SMERSH
article: SMERSH is primarily an espionage organization felt by L. Ron Hubbard to be targeting for sabotage the missions of his Sea Org in the late 1960s. According to Mr. Hubbard, SMERSH was a code name borrowed from James Bond 007 book 'Goldfinger.' Its letters stood for "Soviet, Executive, Murder and so on." "'SMERSH' of course was a fiction," wrote Mr. Hubbard, but "The enemy we fight is not. We call him SMERSH just to be factual and impolite." -- https://www.villagevoice.com/2011/12/23/scientology-on-the-high-seas-yuletide-cheer-including-dickens-adapted-with-evil-psychs/
